<subSubSection id="1F9FAAAC9748A64CE155441FC8CE0BCB" pageId="0" pageNumber="62736" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="602ACFB6D4931833A3B515E08C589C02" pageId="0" pageNumber="62736">Diagnosis</paragraph>
<paragraph id="41F474E0B8C0DD0A1BF6525D37C7AC75" pageId="0" pageNumber="62736">
(
<bibRefCitation id="AD5861124A6D27146E772B54375C2895" author="Costa, Dimitri Araujo" journalOrPublisher="Biociencias (on-line)" pageId="0" pageNumber="62736" pagination="131 - 133" refId="B6421977" refString="Costa, Dimitri Araujo, DeAssis, Jose Eriberto, Christoffersen, Martin Lindsey, 2008. New synonym of Hesione splendida (Hesionidae, Polychaeta, Annelida). Biociencias (on-line) 16 (2): 131 - 133" title="New synonym of Hesione splendida (Hesionidae, Polychaeta, Annelida)" volume="16" year="2008">Costa et al. 2008</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="CF6002BAF3FF996DBF9B9F233BEF2E23" author="Costa, Dimitri Araujo" journalOrPublisher="Gaia Scientia" pageId="0" pageNumber="62736" pagination="166 - 172" refId="B6421968" refString="Costa, Dimitri Araujo, Christoffersen, Martin Lindsey, 2016. Revision and global distribution of Hesione splendida (Annelida, Polychaeta, Hesionidae). Gaia Scientia 10 (4): 166 - 172" title="Revision and global distribution of Hesione splendida (Annelida, Polychaeta, Hesionidae)" volume="10" year="2016">Costa and Christoffersen 2016</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="9866A6E07DA4E10512BABC73FBCF5DF4" author="Imajima, Minoru" journalOrPublisher="National Science Museum Monographs" pageId="0" pageNumber="62736" pagination="1 - 221" refId="B6422669" refString="Imajima, Minoru, 2003. Polychaetous annelids from Sagami Bay and Sagami Sea collected by the Emperor Showa of Japan and deposited at the Showa Memorial Institute, National Science Museum, Tokyo (II): orders included within the Phyllodocida, Amphinomida, Spintherida and Eunicida. National Science Museum Monographs 23: 1 - 221" title="Polychaetous annelids from Sagami Bay and Sagami Sea collected by the Emperor Showa of Japan and deposited at the Showa Memorial Institute, National Science Museum, Tokyo (II): orders included within the Phyllodocida, Amphinomida, Spintherida and Eunicida" volume="23" year="2003">Imajima 2003</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EBE4D6B8FA1FFEBD221ACC9A5B8695BA" author="Salazar-Vallejo, Sergio I." journalOrPublisher="Zoosystema" pageId="0" pageNumber="62736" pagination="227 - 325" refId="B6829589" refString="Salazar-Vallejo, Sergio I., 2018. Revision of Hesione Savigny in Lamarck, 1818 (Annelida, Errantia, Hesionidae). Zoosystema 40 (12): 227 - 325" title="Revision of Hesione Savigny in Lamarck, 1818 (Annelida, Errantia, Hesionidae)" volume="40" year="2018">Salazar-Vallejo 2018</bibRefCitation>
): Prostomium with four eyes, two papilla-like antennae, facial tubercle, nuchal organs and an incision in posterior end. Anterior proboscis ring smooth, carrying two black points in medium-lateral region and a tubercle in the median-posterior region. First segments with eight pairs of modified cirri (&quot;tentacular cirri&quot;) (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A0F477D3ACF3A0939BF56113B2AA1E07" captionStartId="F6439236" pageId="0" pageNumber="62736">4</figureCitation>
<figureCitation id="3611ED548590F417E7DBC6798A0AE7AB" captionStartId="F6439242" pageId="0" pageNumber="62736">b</figureCitation>
). Parapodia sesquiramous-type (notopodial region reduced to cirri and no chaetae); neuropodia with falcigers and dark aciculae. Neurochaetal blades with two teeth-like processes anteriorly, up to 9 times longer than wide.
</paragraph>
